@joshsuko8185 Hey, Josh! I know you’ve been pretty busy answering questions here, so I just wanted to say thank you very much for all the work that you and the rest of your team did to create this awesome and now-nostalgic game. I have many fond memories of playing so many Hot Wheels games including this one and its sequel (Get’n Dirty) throughout my childhood, so it’s a great privilege to be able to communicate with you.

I remember when I saw this game for the first time at a very young age when I watched a cousin of mine play it at his house around 20 years ago, and the gameplay was so fascinating to me that I asked to get my own copy of the game as soon as possible lol. I’m 26 years old now, but I’ve gone through my whole life thus far while having absolutely no idea that the unfinished space-themed level even existed, so learning about secrets like this in games that I used to play many years ago makes going down memory lane by watching gameplay videos like this one even better than I could’ve imagined.

Lastly, I’m not sure who thought of the concept for the intro video, but he/she led us all astray by giving us the false impression that a semi truck would randomly appear at our houses and deliver Hot Wheels play sets to us for free so we could turn all of our rooms/backyards into one big playground of tracks lol. Again, thank you for everything you’ve done, Josh. People like you who made our childhoods fun and memorable by giving us games like Stunt Track Driver will always be greatly appreciated, and we hope you enjoyed working on them just as much as we enjoyed playing them! You’re the best! 🏁🏎️🔥
